/* =========================================
   QUERY 1
   Active products never ordered
   ========================================= */

SELECT
    p.product_id,
    p.product_sku,
    p.product_name,
    p.brand,
    p.list_price,
    p.stock_level
FROM dim_products AS p
LEFT JOIN fact_order_line_items AS li
    ON p.product_id = li.product_id
WHERE p.is_active = 1
  AND li.line_item_id IS NULL
ORDER BY
    p.stock_level DESC,
    p.product_name;


Query Review:
This is a strong extra query that adds useful analytical value to the project.
It is clear, well-structured, and technically correct. The use of LEFT JOIN with NULL filtering works well for 
identifying active products that have never appeared in any order line item. 
The selected columns are relevant for business analysis, and it follows good practice by explicitly naming columns 
instead of using SELECT *.
Ordering by stock_level DESC is also a smart choice, as it helps highlight unsold active products with the highest 
remaining inventory.
Overall, this is a useful extra query for inventory analysis and for identifying potential dead stock or products 
that may need attention.
